ProMED-mail
e-mail: promed@usa.healthnet.org
[The new wheat cultivar should decrease the amount of scabby wheat, and
thus reduce the amount of vomitoxin-affected grain. The pathogen
synthesizes the toxin (deoxynivalenol [DON during the infective process in
the wheat plant. Depending on the concentration of vomitoxin in the grain,
consumption of affected grain induces gastric disturbances and animals may
refuse to eat such grain. The U.S. Food and Drug Administration has
provided information on acceptable levels of vomitoxin in wheat for
consumption by humans, cattle, chickens, swine and other animals. - Mod.DH
